  </study_design_info>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>To prevent an increase in disease activity as measured by anterior cell count, vitreal haze and visual acuity while subjects with stable noninfectious uveitis undergo tapering of concomitant immunosuppressive medications</measure>
    <time_frame>The primary outcome will be assessed at Week 16</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Secondary objectives are to assess changes in visual acuity, retinal thickness, corticosteroid dose, and immunosuppressive drug score. Basiliximab pharmacokinetics and immunogenicity will also be assessed</measure>
    <time_frame>These measures will be assessed at Week 16</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
